ow" class="external text" href="http://www.tapaidiatisgalarias.org">"\xce\xa4\xce\xb1 \xcf\x80\xce\xb1\xce\xb9\xce\xb4\xce\xb9\xce\xac \xcf\x84\xce\xb7\xcf\x82 \xce\xb3\xce\xb1\xce\xbb\xce\xb1\xcf\x81\xce\xaf\xce\xb1\xcf\x82"</a>. Tapaidiatisgalarias.org<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2013-10-17</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALeft+communism&amp;rft.btitle=%CE%A4%CE%B1+%CF%80%CE%B1%CE%B9%CE%B4%CE%B9%CE%AC+%CF%84%CE%B7%CF%82+%CE%B3%CE%B1%CE%BB%CE%B1%CF%81%CE%AF%CE%B1%CF%82&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.pub=Tapaidiatisgalarias.org&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.tapaidiatisgalarias.org&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.blaumachen.gr">"Blaumachen \xe2\x80\x93 journal"</a>. Blaumachen.gr<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2013-10-17</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALeft+communism&amp;rft.btitle=Blaumachen+%E2%80%93+journal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.pub=Blaumachen.gr&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.blaumachen.gr&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Further_reading">Further reading</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Left_communism&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><i>Non-Leninist Marxism: Writings on the Workers Councils</i> (includes texts by <a href="/wiki/Herman_Gorter" title="Herman Gorter">Gorter</a>, <a href="/wiki/Antonie_Pannekoek" title="Antonie Pannekoek">Pannekoek</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sylvia_Pankhurst" title="Sylvia Pankhurst">Pankhurst</a> and <a href="/wiki/Otto_R%C3%BChle" title="Otto R\xc3\xbchle">R\xc3\xbchle</a>), Red and Black Publishers, St Petersburg, Florida, 2007. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-9791813-6-8" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-9791813-6-8">978-0-9791813-6-8</a></li>\n<li>The International Communist Current, itself a Left Communist grouping, has produced a series of studies of what it views as its own antecedents. The book on the German-Dutch current, which is by Philippe Bourrinet (who later left the ICC), in particular contains an exhaustive bibliography.\n<ul>\n<li><i>The Italian Communist Left 1926\xe2\x80\x931945</i> (<a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1897980132" title="Special:BookSources/1897980132">1897980132</a>)</li>\n<li><i>The Dutch-German Communist Left</i> (<a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1899438378" title="Special:BookSources/1899438378">1899438378</a>)</li>\n<li><i>The Russian Communist Left, 1918\xe2\x80\x931930</i> (<a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1897980108" title="Special:BookSources/1897980108">1897980108</a>)</li>\n<li><i>The British Communist Left, 1914\xe2\x80\x931945</i> (<a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1897980116" title="Special:BookSources/1897980116">1897980116</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Also of interest is volume 5 number 4 of Spring 1995 of the journal <i><a href="/wiki/Revolutionary_History" title="Revolutionary History">Revolutionary History</a></i>&#160;: "Through Fascism, War and Revolution: Trotskyism and Left Communism in Italy".</li>\n<li>In addition, there is a good deal of material published on the Internet in various languages. A useful starting point is the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.marxists.org/subject/left-wing/index.htm">Left Communism collection</a> published on the <a href="/wiki/Marxists_Internet_Archive" title="Marxists Internet Archive">Marxists Internet Archive</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<div role="navigation" class="navbox" aria-labelledby="Left_communism" style="padding:3px">\n<table class="nowraplinks collapsible expanded navbox-inner" style="border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit">\n<tr>\n<th scope="col" class="navbox-title" colspan="2" style="background:mistyrose;">\n<div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini">\n<ul>\n<li class="nv-view"><a href="/wiki/Template:Left_communism" title="Template:Left communism"><abbr title="View this template" style=";background:mistyrose;;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none;">v</abbr></a></li>\n<li class="nv-talk"><a href="/wiki/Template_talk:Left_communism" class="mw-redirect" title="Template talk:Left communism"><abbr title="Discuss this template" style=";background:mistyrose;;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none;">t</abbr></a></li>\n<li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Left_communism&amp;action=edit"><abbr title="Edit this template" style=";background:mistyrose;;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none;">e</abbr></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div id="Left_communism" style="font-size:114%;margin:0 4em"><a class="mw-selflink selflink">Left communism</a></div